Classes in clueClient used by clueClient
BoardModel
          Class semantics and roles:
The BoardModel is the Model (as per Java's Model-View-Controller approach to GUI design) for the Clue system.
BoardModel.Card
          Class semantics and roles:
The Card class is an inner class that represents a single card in the gamer's hand.
BoardModel.Cell
          Class semantics and roles:
The Cell class is an inner class that represents a single grid square on the board.
Client
          Class semantics and roles:
The Client represents the entire client-side driver code
The class creates the Client class and the GUI class.
GUI
          Class semantics and roles:
The GUI maintains and manages graphical display for the system.
